#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:7
msgid "Description:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:9
msgid ""
"Provides a simple VTK widget for pyGtk.  This embeds a   vtkRenderWindow "
"inside a GTK widget.  This is based on   vtkTkRenderWidget.py.  The "
"GtkVTKRenderWindowBase class provides the   abstraction necessary for "
"someone to use their own interaction   behaviour.  The method names are "
"similar to those in   vtkInteractorStyle.h."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:16
msgid ""
"The class uses the gtkgl.GtkGLArea widget (gtkglarea).  This avoids   a lot "
"of problems with flicker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:19
msgid "There is a working example at the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:21
msgid "Credits:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:23
msgid ""
"Thanks to Dave Reed for testing the code under various platforms and   for "
"his suggestion to use the GtkGLArea widget to avoid flicker   related issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:27
msgid "Created by Prabhu Ramachandran, March 2001."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:29
msgid "Using GtkGLArea, March, 2002."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:31
msgid "Bugs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:33
msgid ""
"(*) There is a focus related problem.  Tkinter has a focus object   that "
"handles focus events.  I don't know of an equivalent object   under GTK.  "
"So, when an 'enter_notify_event' is received on the   GtkVTKRenderWindow I "
"grab the focus but I don't know what to do when   I get a "
"'leave_notify_event'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/gtk/GtkVTKRenderWindow.py:39
msgid ""
"(*) Will not work under Win32 because it uses the XID of a window in   "
"OnRealize.  Suggestions to fix this will be appreciated."
msgstr ""

